The paper discusses a parallel implementation of a computational problem using the Divide and Conquer paradigm, which is a common topic in Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The problem being solved involves counting triangles in a graph, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the MapReduce programming model, which is a topic in Data Management (cs.DM) and Probabilistic and Randomized Algorithms (cs.PF). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC and cs.DS, followed by cs.DB, cs.DM, and cs.PF.
